{"source_key":"sha256-fff107c46d744695a701c02a06caa1cb","record_index":14,"record_hash":"sha256:10e305ae476fda1d2979af5a6370d12ed9ca800705f1047a65811ad173cab792","timestamp":"2026-05-25T13:15:48.388Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: c64395\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 3857\nOutput:\n# Upstream bug report — `but-agentlog`: most captured turns are never associated with a branch / review target, so a PR view shows only a sparse mid-session fragment\n\n**Component:** `but-agentlog` (capture + GitMeta indexing) — `gitbutlerapp/gitbutler`, `crates/but-agentlog`\n**Related:** `git-meta-lib` (materialization), `but-workspace` (`head_info`)\n**Severity:** 🔴 High — silently drops most of a session from any PR/branch/review lookup; the data *is* captured but is unreachable.\n**Status:** open · needs upstream fix\n**Filed from:** Agent Trail (the public PR-trail viewer that consumes `but_agentlog::projection::project_pr`). This is **not** an Agent Trail bug — Agent Trail faithfully renders whatever turns the projection returns.\n**Discovered:** 2026-05-26, on real data in `[REDACTED:path]`.\n\n---\n\n## TL;DR\n\nA coding-agent session is captured as many *turns*. Each turn is indexed under the branch / review / change targets observed **at the instant that turn is written** (`capture_environment` → `but_workspace::head_info`). When that per-turn workspace observation fails or comes back empty — which it does for the **large majority** of turns in practice — the turn is written with **empty `observed_targets`** and therefore gets **no index entry at all**.\n\nBecause the public projection matches turns **individually** by target index (`projection.rs`: `if reasons.is_empty() { continue }`), those un-indexed turns are invisible to every PR / branch / review lookup. The transcript bodies are stored fine; they just can't be found by the facet a reviewer uses.\n\n**Concrete:** on the fixture below, a real ~7+ prompt Codex session (`sha256-8466d00c…`) appears in the entire index **exactly twice** — two mid-session turns. The earlier turns (and several later ones) carry no target index, so a viewer for that session's PR shows only those 2 turns and is missing \"the\n[TRUNCATED]\nted. This directly fixes \"the beginning is missing.\"\n3. **Surface association coverage.** Record, per session, how many turns are associated vs total (analogous to the existing `RecordCoverage`[REDACTED:path] signals) so consumers can warn \"N of M turns are not associated with this PR\" instead of silently showing a fragment.\n4. **Have `project_pr` also resolve `change` targets** (`projection.rs:36-47`), or guarantee that any turn indexed under a change is also indexed under its branch/review. Secondary, but closes a real coverage gap.\n\n---\n\n## Verification checklist (for the fix)\n\n- A fresh capture of an on-branch session indexes **every** turn under that branch's `ref:` target (not just a couple). Check:\n  `SELECT COUNT(*) FROM set_values sv JOIN metadata m ON sv.metadata_id=m.rowid WHERE m.key='gitbutler:agentlog-index:v1:branch:sha256-<hash of ref:refs/heads/<branch>>';` equals the session's `turn:*` count.\n- `project_pr` for that PR returns turns spanning the **whole** session, including the first prompt.\n- Turns captured before a PR exists become visible after the PR/branch association lands (back-fill).\n- `observed_targets` is non-empty whenever the repo is on a resolvable branch (no silent `ObservedTargets::default()` on the common path).\n\n---\n\n## Appendix — key code references\n\n| What | Location (`crates/but-agentlog/src/…`) |\n|---|---|\n| Per-turn capture + index write | `gitmeta/write.rs:187-215` (and the second copy `:380-396`) |\n| `observed_target_index_keys` | `gitmeta/write.rs:301` |\n| `capture_environment` | `environment.rs:129` |\n| `environment_from_parts` (empties `observed_targets` on workspace error) | `environment.rs:143-190` |\n| `workspace_snapshot` / `head_info` | `environment.rs:222-243` |\n| `review_targets` (branch/PR/review-id keys) | `environment.rs` (`fn review_targets`) |\n| Index key hashing (`gitbutler:agentlog-index:v1:<kind>:sha256-<hex>`) | `gitmeta/mod.rs:123-134` |\n| Per-turn match filter + review/branch-only lookup | `projection.rs:88-99`, `:36-47` (pinned rev `c95ea55`) |\n","tool_name":"exec_command","tool_kind":"exec","tool_input":null,"exit_code":0,"outcome":"succeeded","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-25T13:15:48.388Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}